<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Kelsea Ballerini oozed showbiz glamour as she hit the ACM Awards red carpet in Nashville this Wednesday.</p>

<p>The 27-year-old country blonde showed off her knockout legs at the socially distant event in an elaborate sequined dress.</p>

<p>She unleashed her animal instinct with a bit of black leopard print over a deep purple and rust-colored background.</p>

<p>Sizzling sensation: Kelsea Ballerini oozed showbiz glamour as she hit the ACM Awards red carpet in Nashville this Wednesday</p>

<p>Her ensemble featured raised shoulders reminiscent of the 1980s as well as a Grecian chic sash draped across the front.</p>

<p>The sash was buckled to her waistline at the middle and then dangled down past the hemline of her shimmering skirt.</p>

<p>Sweeping her blonde hair into a fashionable updo she rounded off the look with a pair of leopard print cowgirl boots.</p>

<p>The awards show extravaganza will blend live and pre-taped segments and be held across three Nashville landmarks, facilitating social distancing.</p>

<p>When you got it: The 27-year-old country blonde showed off her knockout legs at the socially distant event in an elaborate sequined dress</p>

<p>One site is the Ryman Auditorium which is where Kelsea was pictured, and the others were the Grand Ole Opry and Bluebird Cafe.</p>

<p>Earlier this week Kelsea was corporate chic in a pinstripe getup as she gave a virtual radio interview in Nashville and dished about her upcoming red carpet look.</p>

<p>'What's so funny about this is, this outfit is something that I was gonna wear on a carpet before the world shut down,' she spilled to Radio.com.</p>

<p>'And I told my stylist, I was like: "Hold this outfit, 'cause it's too good and I don't - don't send it back, like, just wait," and it was perfect for this,' said Kelsea. </p>

<p>Looking fab: Earlier this week Kelsea was corporate chic in a pinstripe getup as she gave a virtual radio interview in Nashville and dished about her upcoming red carpet look</p>

<p>'But it's like this dress and these matching sequin boots. They're like red sequin cowgirl boots. They're bad-A,' she gushed.</p>

<p>Kelsea, who won the Gene Weed Milestone award at the ACM Awards three years ago, is up for the best female vocalist gong this year.</p>

<p>She is competing in a formidable category for the prize, facing off against Miranda Lambert, Carrie Underwood, Kacey Musgraves and Maren Morris.</p>

<p>Kelsea released her new album ballerini last Friday and performed onstage at the Ryman Auditorium during the awards show - however her song of choice was this May's single Hope In A Bottle from her album Kelsea which she dropped in March.</p>

